    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-18T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="750"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/11–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-18T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 18, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 18—5:13 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2465. ReDeptel 1938 repeated Nanking 1635.<note n="52" xml:id="d750fn52">November
                        16, 6 p. m., above.</note> Mukden radio transmitter seized today. Mukden
                    notified monitor newscast frequencies and will follow same procedure as Dairen
                    traffic.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2465; repeated Nanking 1864.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
